name: DEWI RATIH
description: Dewi Ratih is the moon goddess in Javanese Hindu culture and Balinese mythology. It is also said that she is the goddess of beauty. The famous myth about Dewi Ratih is about a lunar eclipse. At the time of the eclipse, Dewi Ratih who was running in heaven was caught by Kala Rau. He was chased because it was he who told the god Vishnu that Kala Rau wanted to drink from Tirta Amertha (Water of eternal life).
